@node "attributes" "Device - Attributes"

      unit

The unit we opened as passed to new().

      io

The iorequest that was created via CreateIORequest(). If NIL, the device could
not be opened.

      flags

The flags as passed to new().

      lasterror

After the execution of a device command this attribute is a copy of the error
entry of the io. Not necessary.
@endnode

@node "methods" "Device - Methods"

      select(list,index)

Select accepts the following tags:

  "name"    - sets the device name
  "flag"    - the special flags
  "unit"    - the unit to be opened

      open(name, unit, flags)

Open the device with the according parameters. May raise the following
exceptions, exceptioninfo:

  "dev", -2     CreateMsgPort() failed
  "dev", -3     CreateIORequest() failed
  "dev", -4     OpenDevice() failed

If one of those exceptions is raised, the device couldn't be opened.

      close()

Closes the device, deletes the IORequest and frees the message port (in this
order). After calling this method you have to open the device again.

      doio(), sendio(), abortio()

Calls the according exec functions.

      reset()

Resets the device.

      end()

Calls close().
@endnode

